-- Velarde Sees Zero Peru Inflation in January, Peru21 Reports
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-01-30T15:34:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/velarde-sees-zero-peru-inflation-in-january-peru21-reports.html
Peru will post zero inflation this
month after food prices declined, Peru21  reported , citing
comments by central bank President Julio Velarde.  The annual  inflation  rate may fall to 4.3 percent this
month and return to the central bank’s target range before the
end of the first half, according to the Lima-based newspaper
said, which cited Velarde’s comments in an interview with
television station Canal N.  The central bank targets annual inflation in a range of 1
percent to 3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in  Lima  at 
